pageContext.description: Dimensions: L 107mm; We 65.2; Wm 39; Bm 42.9; min Blp 7.7; DS 72.3,Typology: spasmodic flattening of upper m-m, but largely biconical; 3 rib motif - some bowed if not evenly spaced - disappear before joining lower m-m; rounded body angles; lp. little asymm.; narrow rect. s. end.,Manufacture: few hmks. discernible on lower bl. face, assoc. with bulge in sides just above expanded bl. e., but no bl. tip hollows; thin cg. fl. stump along much of sides, little wavy and asym.; flattening of thick cg. fl. at m. causing some lipping - inside and out.,Condition: edge intact, fairly sharp - 2 small nicks prob. mod. interference,Attached Material: areas with chalky accretion, also mid-brown soil traces.
pageContext.surface: Mainly varied green dry surface, some textured, overlying black-green patina, exposed in patches.
